Upscale Bar and Grill with comfort food that will please. I have come here many times before and the drinks are always good and the service is always friendly and fast. We have had their pizza many times and it is very tasty. We also had their nachos which were fantastic too. Last night we went here for my mother in laws birthday and at first she was not pleased by the fact we were at a bar but the food ultimately won her over. I am very picky about my pizza now being from Chicago and they by far have the best extra thin pizza. The crust is crispy but not cardboard like. My one complaint is that for a medium pizza each topping cost 2.25 which took the price from 11$ to 21$ easily and it wasnt packed on the pizza. I know a whole green pepper don't cost $2.25. They need to readjust this price. We had beers margaritas and cocktails which all were 9$ or less. The have certain specials on certain days of the week as well.  We ordered chips and salsa along with wings. The wings were sweet hott. My man devoured them and the sauce was peppery. The meat for me was a tad dry but the flavor was great.The madd jacks sandwhich which was fantastic with wonderly fried chicken and an amazing sauce was ordered as well. The ONLY thing that came out wrong was the baked mostaccoli for the bday girl. It was not baked and the sauce was essentially hunts tomato sauce with some sugar thrown in. Being Italian I know what a sauce should taste like...that was not it. She hated it so we sent it back and they were very kind and took it off the bill.  The music they play is eclectic and people of all races can be found here. There are giant projectors playing sports and many other things as well. I have never experienced the outside patio area but this summer I may stop in to hang out for a few.
